every defect of its cho&s;en object, during the &s;ea&s;on
of pa&s;&s;ion: from her, therefore, this an&s;wer, leaving
unob&s;erved the littlene&s;s and &s;pleen which compo&s;ed
it, retained but &s;o much of meaning as belongs to
announcing jealou&s;y, and in giving him that idea, filled
