I forgive him.&endq;</P>
<P>Indiana was &s;o much piqued, &s;he could &s;carce
refrain from relating the portico hi&s;tory at lord
Pervil's; but the Baronet, not remarking her di&s;|compo&s;ure,
turned to Camilla and Eugenia, &s;mi|lingly
exclaiming: &startq;Well, my dear girls, I &s;ha'n't
mention what we have been looking at in your
ab&s;ence, becau&s;e of your blu&s;hes, which I hope
